				<td colspan="2"><span>Ok this is a bit of a rant, but Augmentation enhancing is seriously bothering me.
<br />

<br />
First off:  Grats shaman on cornering the market on billions of plats in augments.  Thanx SOE for making a huge upgrade path available only through 1 class.
<br />

<br />
Second:  Once you manage to find a shaman willing to do the combine for less than an arm and a leg (with AAs', alchemy etc.  we all know how common they are....)  THANK you SOE for making the primary component SOOOOOOOOOO insanely rare.  
<br />

<br />
Yes, you can make some uber augments, but jesus, you gotta find a qualified shaman.  Gather up an aug (semi easy w. the bazaar).  Get the other pieces  (semi-bummer)  and then find a Discordant Scoriae.
<br />

<br />
And I'm sorry.  That item is WAY to rare.  It's a joke and a slap in the face for anyone who wishes to even ATTEMPT the combine.  
<br />

<br />
Anyone else noticing this.  </span></td>
